    "narrative": "Today's strongest play is clearly **Corbin Carroll**, who boasts an elite 85.9 score against the Rockies' **M\u00e1rquez**. This matchup features a significantly favorable **SP_xERA** of 5.26, which contributes a substantial +19% boost to his score. Adding to his advantage are a dynamic platoon advantage (+6%) and the benefits of slow pitcher delivery (+4%), which is particularly relevant given his elite speed. His #3 batting order slot also provides a +6% bump, solidifying his status as today's top option.\n\nOther strong contenders include **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.9) and **Brice Turang** (65.4). **Pasquantino** benefits from a favorable park, a strong matchup against **Urena** (+18% SP Skill), and a dynamic platoon advantage (+14%) that pushes his score into the recommended start range. **Turang** also lands in the strong tier thanks to his #1 lineup spot (+10%), a dynamic platoon advantage (+3%), and decent matchup metrics, despite a slight park ding. **Seiya Suzuki** (66.2) presents a compelling case as well, with his +19% SP Skill against **Sasaki**'s high **SP_xERA** overcoming a slight platoon disadvantage.\n\nThe most interesting bench decision involves **Austin Riley**, whose 43.6 score was just shy of making the cut. While he benefits from a favorable park and a dynamic platoon, the elite opposing pitcher **Wheeler** (2.73 **SP_xERA**) significantly suppressed his score (-19%). This, coupled with a slight penalty for batting behind an elite catcher, pushed him below other options. Meanwhile, **Mickey Moniak** is flagged as a RAINOUT, making him an automatic bench given the postponement. Keep an eye on **Jose Caballero** (44.5) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (49.6) as marginal plays who might see increased opportunity if any game-time decisions arise, though their respective lineup spots and platoon matchups are working against them today.",
